                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I find I'm perpetually poor, because I've never bought or sold anything in the bazaar.  If I can't use something I usually give it away to someone in my guild, a friend, or donate it to the guild bank.  I wear a green silken drape at lvl 53, and that twilight cape that dropped the other night on shadow island while I was trying to quest the wizard robe was a nice surprise, because it was an upgrade, and not just something to sell for pp.  I don't enjoy buying and selling.  I couldn't care less what the prices are for anything, but my spells, but I suspect I'll manage to get a hold of them without paying a huge price.  <br /><br />Why you ask?  Because I'm actually rich.  Rich in the number of friends I've made that think of me when a necro spell drops, and nobody in their guild needs it.  I've gotten several spells this way, and have yet to ding to a new spell circle without having all my spells already.  I think I've actually got all but a few up to lvl 56 already.  A few from one person in particular, which came my way because I passed on the FBSS in lower guk once, so the warrior who really wanted it, and was there to get it, could have it.  It made me feel good, and I made a good friend that night.  I think it went for 4k at the time.  4x more money than I've ever had in my bank.<br /><br />Other than spells I don't care about loot much.  The loot will come from just playing, and winning rolls on items when something drops that I need.  I don't give things away expecting to get re paid down the line, but more often then not, that's what happens.  I'm not posting this to say I'm better than anyone else, or take on a holier than thou attitude.  I just enjoy playing this way.  Buying items takes the fun out of getting them for me.  Whether I'm paying in pp, or $$, it's all the same to me.  I could go to ebay and be uber in a day if I wanted, but what fun would that be?  I'd probably quit playing a week later.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
